GSM 850 / 900 / 1800 / 1900 - SIM 1 & SIM 2 (dual-SIM model only). HSDPA 850 / 900 / 1900 / 2100. 154 x 86 x 6.4 mm (6.06 x 3.39 x 0.25 in). Single SIM (Micro-SIM) or Dual SIM (Micro-SIM, dual stand-by). 5.0 inches, 75.7 cm 2 (~57.1% screen-to-body ratio). 480 x 854 pixels, 16:9 ratio (~187 ppi density). microSD, up to 32 GB (dedicated slot). 8 GB, 1 GB RAM 16 GB, 2 GB RAM. (October 2016) ( Learn how and when to remove this template message ). Acer Z520 is a high-end smartphone made by Acer Inc. much slimmer than IPhone 4. GHz Mediatek MT6582 quad core, 2.3. GHz dual-core NVIDIA Tegra Denver or 1.4. GHz Qualcomm Snapdragon 320 and can underclock to 1.2. GHz (for MTK Only) and the graphics was ARM Mali-400 , ULP GeForce with tesselation, instant rendering and vertex array object from OpenGL ES 3.0, or else Adreno 320. For Liquid variant, it uses 1.6. GHz dual core Intel Atom with PowerVR SGX 544MP2. RAM is 1 GB and in Liquid 2 GB.. At 2014, it would be now update to 4.4.4 Kitkat for liquid variants and uses 1.6. GHz 64-bit Quad-Core Snapdragon S4 play with Adreno 320 and original variant update to 5.0 Lollipop. Unofficial updates in 7.0 Nougat for better stability phones.. Acer Z520 uses 2G , 3G , and 4G-HSPA+. The top speed in 2G was 1024 kbit/s downlink and 768 kbit/s uplink. In 3G, the top speed was 14.2 MB/s downlink and 7.6 MB/s uplink. In 4G - HSPA+ , the top speed was 26.4 MB/s downlink and 13.2 MB/s uplink. Bluetooth hardware is Mediatek which supports up to 50 meters and WIFI is Ralink which also supports up to 120 meters.. The total frames per second is 57.4 fps whilst enhanced with Butter gets 58.5 fps.. The total frames per second is 57.5 fps whilst enhanced with Butter gets 59.3 fps.. It tied with IPhone 3GS and IPhone 4 the score was 1-3. In NVIDIA, gets 3-2 tied with others, then Qualcomm gets 3-3.. The 2.3 gets 12248, 3.3.1, 13392, 4.0, 14432, 5.0, 15530.. Home Mobiles Phone Finder Acer Liquid Z520. SPECIFICATIONS USER REVIEWS NEWS. Share on Facebook Tweet Share Share Email Reddit. Acer Liquid Z520 smartphone was launched in March 2015. The phone comes with a 5.00-inch touchscreen display with a resolution of 480 pixels by 800 pixels at a PPI of 187 pixels per inch. The Acer Liquid Z520 is powered by 1.3GHz quad-core Qualcomm Snapdragon 400 processor and it comes with 1GB of RAM. The phone packs 8GB of internal storage that can be expanded up to 32GB via a microSD card. As far as the cameras are concerned, the Acer Liquid Z520 packs a 8-megapixel primary camera on the rear and a 2-megapixel front shooter for selfies. The Acer Liquid Z520 runs Android 5.0. The Acer Liquid Z520 is a single SIM (GSM). Connectivity options include Wi-Fi, GPS, Bluetooth, FM and 3G. Sensors on the phone include Proximity sensor, Accelerometer and Ambient light sensor.. Acer Liquid Z520 Review Hands on features, specs, price, camera test, performance. GSM 850 / 900 / 1800 / 1900 - SIM 1 & SIM 2. 86 x 154 x 6.4 mm. Acer Liquid Z520 brings joy to entry level smartphone users. 5.0 inch TFT touchscreen with resolution support up to 480 x 854 pixels (187 ppi). Mediatek MT6582M Quad-core processor with 1.3 GHz clock speed. 1 GB of RAM, Mali-400MP2 graphics, and 8 GB of internal memory expandable up to 16 GB. Primary camera is an 8 MP unit with LED flash and autofocus, secondary is a 2 MP unit. Additional camera aid features include face detection, HDR, Panorama, etc. For connectivity there is micro-USB v2.0, Bluetooth v4.0, Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n. Colors in which this model is available are basic black and white. Reasons for popularity in the Philippines. As the smartphone era continues to expand, increasing numbers of brands are putting their best foot forward to create an impact like none other. In Philippines, Acer has found a new footing in the market with their exceptional range of smart devices that offer impeccable value for money. This Taiwanese multinational brand has played all the right moves and landed themselves in various corners of the world while experiencing tremendous success. The Acer Liquid Z520 is one such model that went largely praises within just a couple of months due to which it is now considered to be one of their best sellers.. Currently headquartered in Hsinchu City, Taiwan, Acer was founded by Stan Shih and his wife Carolyn Yeh. Starting out small with just 11 employees and total of $25,000 in capital, it head out to the world soon as a PC manufacturer. Couple decades later, Acer is now of the world leaders in technology and tech based products.. This gorgeous model is not only visually attractive, but it also packs a great amount of punch to sideline a lot of other models within the same price range. Some features that it boasts are as follows:. One of the reasons why Acer Liquid Z520 is popular is because it is an entry level smartphone that is offered at an exceptionally lower price tag. People who are planning to purchase their first android device, or those who want a backup model to their high-end phones mainly buy the Z520. As there is no shortage of phone elitists in the Philippines, Acer enjoys a favourable reputation, brought forward from their computer and tablet segments. It's a phone packing a 5-inch at its front- which is a good point at start. The handset is another addition to its line-up to budget segment which seemingly put up a good stand in the smart market.. The Acer Liquid Z520 fronting a fairly large 5-inch screen with a resolution of 480x854 pixels, which is a bit disappointing. Under the hood is the MediaTek SoC quad-core processor with a clock speed of 1.3GHz paired with 1GB of RAM and 8GB expandable storage up to 32GB via microSD card. Though this handset seems not a great performer, however, it navigates on Android v4.4 KitKat and features a good quality camera of 8MP at the rear and 2MP on front which is a good tool for shooting selfies. If you're really on a tight budget, then this Acer Liquid Z520 is worthy of consideration.. Considering the price status of Acer Liquid Z520, considerable minor issues comes as package which is expectable for a budget ranged handset. Issues include insufficiency in battery backup and memory capacity, annoying floaters, ads, and preloaded software, blocked features, dreary visual skins, custom ROM and stuttering slow performance. Hands-on - Hands-on + Android - Android + MWC2015 - MWC2015 +. There aren't many Android phones that can offer a large screen at a low price. This is the goal Acer 's aiming at with the Liquid Z520 – a 109-euro ($118) phone packing a 5-incher at its front. But what do you actually get for this kind of money?. The answer is a rectangular-ish, plasticky smartphone with low-end specifications. On one hand, the Acer Liquid Z520 is not a beauty contest winner and it is also on the chubby side. But on the other, the phone has a good grip to it thanks to its textured back cover. Don't hold your breath for the screen on this guy. Sure, it is fairly large, but its resolution is just 480 by 854 pixels, which is disappointing. We also noticed fingerprint smudge sticking to its surface rather easily.. A peek under the hood of the Acer Liquid Z520 reveals a 1.3GHz quad-core MediaTek SoC (as indicated by the CPU-Z app) along with 1GB of RAM and 8GB of expandable storage. We did notice some stuttering while checking out the handset , which hints that the phone isn't a great performer and might lag when pushed. The phone runs Android 4.4 KitKat with a pretty stock-ish feel to it, although we noticed a few additions to it, including DTS audio tweaks and a redesigned recent apps menu where space for shortcuts and up to nine recent items has been made. On the back of the Acer Liquid Z520 we find an 8MP camera, while a 2MP front-facing cam is used for shooting selfies.. And that's the Acer Liquid Z520 in a nutshell. If your budget is extremely tight, this could be an option worth considering, although our advice would be to spend a few bucks extra on something a bit more capable in the hardware department.. Acer Liquid Z520 Reviews. Liquid Z520 features 5" display with Android 4.4.2 KitKat, Quad Core 1.3GHz Processor and 8GB memory.. Please feel free to post your review on this product.. nasira z520 ko charge lng kinabukasan di na mag power .pinaayos k 4600 hingi price phone 4990 hehehe para bili na din bago,. Maganda, durable, and of course affordable. For a highscool student like me na medyo careless. , andaming beses na nyang nabagsak na pa-plakda and it is sooooooo durable. About the battery hahahaha, as the time pass mas palala ng palala yung mabilis na pag low bat. nya pero ayos lang mag o-one year na sya pero hhehe bumugay rin, basa lang pala ang katapat pero, nice, great, mauulit.. The screen has a bad angle, when the phone is tilted in a certain angle the screen is dimming, like in a laptop if you are viewing on the edge of the screen. This is a down for me specially if you are a gamer and looking for a budget phone, if you are playing a racing game, Traffic Rider to be specific, it is really annoying and a pain the eyes. Also if you are watching a video with your friends those who are on your left (if you rotate your phone with the Acer logo is on the left) won't see the video because of this bad angle.. Camera is good compared to other brand with the same specs of 8mp main and 2mp front. Acer z520 has a decent cam quality, not too much saturation and not much pixelated.. Video recording is not that good and the downside is the output video is to big, it'll consume storage space, a 3mins or 5mins video would consume 20-50mb of your storage.. 4 months ago I would charge the phone at least one or two times a day, but now it drains quickly and would have to charge three times. Maybe because of the game I'm playing requiring internet connection. But if you're just checking social media from time to time, from 8am with 100% battery, you would have 23%-15% at 6pm.. Storage doesn't support USB OTG, but has a feature where you could move some apps to SD card, which is good since the internal storage is only 8gb.. RAM usage would peak from time to time which is kinda annoying, there are times when only chrome browser were opened and RAM usage would peak to 80%, causing the phone to overheat, and would drain the battery fast.. The recent task feature where you can clear all running and recent task is good, you don't have to flick each window to remove from the list.. The floating widgets (calculator) is great, you can use it in any running app and you can minimize so you could multi task.. Audio is good depending on what you're playing, other videos or music would be loud others wouldn't.. From the time i bought it at php4990, I guess i didn't get what I paid for.. My virdict is the Acer z520 is an okay phone, if you're a selfie lord this is quite good phone, if you're a gamer, just add a few thousands and look for atleast an octacore with 2gb RAM or a QUADCORE with 2gb RAM.. Super ganda and tagal malowbat try to test dont based on comments here. guys try to test acer z520 sobrang tagal malowbat, wag po kayo maniniwala sa mga nagkokoment na mabilis malobat acer.. sbrang ganda rn design txt and call ayus walang lag,, kaht sa txt mas prefer ko sya kensa local brands natn dto ph. kakainis lang mga messages dto na mabilis daw malobat sakin 2-3 days mabils ba un? kaya yun sa over all specs maganda xa kaya considered xa as an international brand. 154 x 86 x 6.4 mm. Android OS v4.4.2 ( KitKat ). 8 MP 3264 x 2448 px autofocus. 850 / 900 / 1800 / 1900. DroidChart.com / Smartphones / Acer / Acer Liquid Z520 (2015). 5 inches 480 x 854 px. The detailed specifications, photos and introductory video of the Acer Liquid Z520 (Z520). The list of the competitors most often compared to the Acer Liquid Z520 smartphone.. The Acer Liquid Z520 (Z520) smartphone released in 2015. It is powered by Mediatek MT6582M chipset, 1 GB of RAM and 8 GB of internal storage.. The Acer Liquid Z520 runs on Android OS v4.4.2 (KitKat) out of the box. It comes with a Li-Po 2000 mAh battery. It features a 5 inches TFT display with 480 x 854 px resolution. A thin-film-transistor (TFT) LCD display is a variant of a liquid-crystal display (LCD).. The Acer Liquid Z520 runs on Android OS v4.4.2 (KitKat) out of the box, but the Liquid Z520's firmware can be upgraded to a newer version of OS.. Screen size is measured in inches, diagonally from corner to corner. The 5 inches TFT capacitive touch screen with 480 x 854 px resolution is multitouch capable.. The smartphone's memory (1 GB) cannot be expanded, but the storage (8 GB) can be expanded with a microSD card.. The camera of the Acer Liquid Z520 is equipped with autofocus. Autofocus is a camera feature that fine-tunes the focus of the camera, it is a nice feature of this smartphone.. This smartphone has a built-in GPS receiver. GPS is a satellite based navigation system that allows the determination of the exact geographical location on Earth. This Acer smartphone has FM radio receiver.. The Li-Po 2000 mAh battery gives the smartphone a good battery backup.. The smartphone sensors measure physical quantities and transmit them to the application processor. The phones's accelerometer is a built-in electronic component that measures tilt and motion. The proximity sensor detects when a user is holding the phone near their face during a call and turns off the display to prevent keypad presses and battery consumption from the display. The Liquid Z520 has Dual SIM capability, which means that you can insert two different SIM cards and use them both from one phone.. Compare Acer Liquid Z520 to other smartphones. The specifications above are based on the official data published by the manufacturer, but we also take user reviews into consideration. Switch off the cell phone by holding down the Power rocker for a short while. Afterwards press and hold together Volume Down +. Power button for several seconds. You should release held keys when the Boot Mode appears. From the menu on the screen select option Recovery , by using Volume Up to scroll and Volume Down to confirm. When an Android Image displays on the screen press the Power button. Use Volume Down to choose " wipe data/factory reset ", and then push the Power button to confirm. Select " Yes--delete all user data ". Use Volume buttons to scroll and Power key to choose. To restart the tablet, select " reboot system now ". Success! The hard reset is done.
